1
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,433
<i>What did you do
to Jessica this time?</i>

2
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:38,500
<i>You hurt her again, didn't you?</i>

3
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:39,867
<i> Manuel, our daughter...</i>

4
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,867
<i>Coleen pushed her
into the street.</i>

5
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,833
<i>Our daughter is fighting
for her life!</i>

6
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:47,733
<i> Sweetheart, please fight.</i>

7
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:48,833
<i> Don't give up.</i>

8
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:51,233
<i>Mom, you shouldn't have
left dad with Hazel.</i>

9
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:54,267
<i>Do you really think
she'd take your dad away?</i>

10
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:57,000
<i>Hazel would never leave Jessica
behind.</i>

11
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:59,733
<i>Even the worst mother
in the world would never</i>

12
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:03,033
<i>abandon her child when
their life is on the line.</i>

13
00:01:03,167 --> 00:01:05,033
<i> We're right here.</i>

14
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:07,033
<i> We're waiting for you.</i>

15
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,833
<i> I love you so much.</i>

16
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:16,200
<i>- No! No! No! No! No!
- Jessica!</i>

17
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:17,367
<i> Please, Doctor!</i>

18
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,833
<i> Code blue! Code blue!</i>

19
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,833
<i> Jessica's gone.</i>

20
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:22,100
<i> Oh my God.</i>

21
00:01:22,233 --> 00:01:24,633
<i> My daughter needs me!</i>

22
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:25,633
<i> Let go of me!</i>

23
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:26,400
<i> Manuel, no! Don't! Don't!</i>

24
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:27,700
<i> Let go of me!</i>

25
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,333
<i> We know Hazel.</i>

26
00:01:29,467 --> 00:01:33,633
<i>We just need to prove
Coleen didn't push Jessica.</i>

27
00:01:33,767 --> 00:01:34,733
<i> But...</i>

28
00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:36,867
<i>She could twist Jessica
and Coleen's fight</i>

29
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,367
<i> into something bigger.</i>

30
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,533
<i>Make it appear as though
Coleen had a motive.</i>

31
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:44,300
<i> She could send me to jail.</i>

32
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:50,367
Here.

33
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,833
Put it here.

34
00:01:57,267 --> 00:01:58,433
Thank you.

35
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,700
Guys.

36
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,633
<i> Over here, too.</i>

37
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,800
What is this?

38
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:21,300
Why isn't anything ready yet?

39
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,333
The guests will be here
any minute.

40
00:02:25,167 --> 00:02:26,533
Look at these chairs!

41
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:28,567
They should've been
arranged hours ago!

42
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:33,833
Hazel, please rest for now.
We've got this.

43
00:02:33,967 --> 00:02:34,767
No.

44
00:02:35,433 --> 00:02:36,667
If you can't do it, I will.

45
00:02:38,367 --> 00:02:40,867
I want everything to be
perfect for Jessica.

46
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,533
Jessica, dear...

47
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,367
forgive me.

48
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:11,167
Forgive me for not
protecting you.

49
00:03:11,933 --> 00:03:13,600
For not saving you.

50
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:19,933
I have sinned against you
in ways I can't undo.

51
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:22,333
I was always the one
who hurt you.

52
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,833
Yelling, pushing you away.

53
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:29,767
I never showed you
or told you that I love you.

54
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,433
It's too late.

55
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,133
It's all too late.

56
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:41,933
But even if it's too late,
I will make it right.

57
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:48,533
I will make it up to you
and make Coleen pay.

58
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,433
Coleen and everyone
who killed you.

59
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,833
Friend.

60
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,533
Please don't let your
first thought be revenge.

61
00:03:58,667 --> 00:04:01,933
Let's spend these last
moments with Jessica in peace.

62
00:04:02,067 --> 00:04:05,067
Take this time to be with her
while we still can.

63
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:07,867
My anger doesn't care
about place or time.

64
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:13,767
I can grieve while I plan
how to make them pay.

65
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:22,533
Come here.

66
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,867
Do you think she's here?

67
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:38,700
I'm sure of it.

68
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:41,467
Coleen always comes here when
she's going through something.

69
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:43,967
She must be nearby.

70
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:44,967
Is that her?

71
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:47,467
<i> Coleen?</i>

72
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:49,033
<i> Coleen!</i>

73
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:50,733
Sweetie!

74
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:53,400
Dear.

75
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:05,233
Are you okay?

76
00:05:08,567 --> 00:05:12,733
Attorney Yeban said
if Hazel files a suit,

77
00:05:12,867 --> 00:05:14,533
you just have to be
consistent with everything

78
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:16,067
you tell the court.

79
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:22,333
You must remember every
single detail of what happened,

80
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:23,633
even the tiniest thing. Okay?

81
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:31,567
Sweetie, you have to remember.

82
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:33,167
You're innocent.

83
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:38,800
Andrea, I can't help
feeling guilty.

84
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:42,633
I couldn't save Jessica.

85
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:44,333
You never wanted that.

86
00:05:45,367 --> 00:05:48,467
I really never wanted it.

87
00:05:49,233 --> 00:05:53,167
But I followed Jessica
out of the hospital.

88
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:56,900
I kept pestering her,
trying to make her talk to me.

89
00:05:57,033 --> 00:06:01,900
Even if I'm innocent,
I'm still the reason she's gone.

90
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:03,100
It's my fault.

91
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:04,200
Coleen.

92
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,800
Come on. That's enough!

93
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:08,467
Stop it.

94
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:12,467
Stop blaming yourself. You have
done nothing wrong. Nothing.

95
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:18,400
It's easy for you to say
that because you weren't there!

96
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:20,367
What about me?

97
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:24,133
I saw how Jessica got hit!

98
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:28,133
So don't tell me
not to feel guilty.

99
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,300
It's so hard not to.

100
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,833
- Coleen.
- Coleen! Coleen!

101
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,333
Let her be for a moment.

102
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:42,833
We need to talk about
what to do next.

103
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:48,100
We have to get the CCTV
footage from the accident.

104
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:51,267
So that Coleen can corroborate
everything she'll say.

105
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,833
And also to find out
exactly what happened.

106
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:58,467
What about
Colonel Sarabia?

107
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:01,500
Doesn't he know someone
at the Traffic Authority?

108
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:05,333
- Maybe he can get a copy.
- Okay.

109
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:09,333
<i>I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

110
00:07:09,467 --> 00:07:11,233
<i> - Please try again later.
</i>- I can't reach him.

111
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:14,267
I actually have a contact
at the Manila Traffic Authority,

112
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:15,733
Brix's brother.

113
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:18,567
If they have footage
of the crash, I'll get it.

114
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,367
I promise we'll secure it.

115
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:30,700
Felma,

116
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,233
please come with me
to Jessica's wake.

117
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:38,533
Let's tell Dr. Richard.

118
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:42,233
I don't need permission.
I have to see my daughter.

119
00:07:42,367 --> 00:07:43,367
But, Manuel...

120
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,300
No! I'm going to Jessica now.

121
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:48,233
If you won't come with me,

122
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,500
I will crawl out
of this hospital.

123
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:53,367
I'll do whatever it takes
just so I can see my child.

124
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:01,633
<i> Coleen?</i>

125
00:08:02,733 --> 00:08:04,933
Coleen, please open the door.

126
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:08,367
<i> Maybe we shouldn't force her.</i>

127
00:08:10,467 --> 00:08:11,567
It's understandable.

128
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:14,867
She's feeling guilty.

129
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,533
I don't get it, Jeff. Why now?

130
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:24,333
Just when we'd finally started
to heal as a family,

131
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:26,700
this had to happen.

132
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:32,867
We'll never have Jessica
with us again.

133
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:39,100
We won't get to be a real sister
and brother to her anymore.

134
00:08:39,967 --> 00:08:42,333
Why did it have to be her?

135
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:44,567
Why her, of all people?

136
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,933
<i> Why not Hazel?</i>

137
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:49,367
I know that sounds terrible,

138
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:52,367
but that's what I think
sometimes.

139
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,900
I thought the same.

140
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,133
I wanted to be the one
to spoil Jessica,

141
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:03,600
to be her big brother
the way I'd spoil Coleen.

142
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:26,833
Mrs. Cruz.

143
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:17,733
The nerve of you people.

144
00:10:18,867 --> 00:10:21,800
If you don't want to be
embarrassed, get out.

145
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:26,400
I have every right to be here.

146
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,900
That's my child in the casket.

147
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:30,767
With these people?

148
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,533
No.

149
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,167
I won't allow it.

150
00:10:37,033 --> 00:10:38,900
And you, Coleen.

151
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:40,167
Where's your sense of shame?

152
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:43,900
You're the reason
Jessica is dead.

153
00:10:44,033 --> 00:10:45,500
You pushed her.

154
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:48,500
I didn't push her.

155
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,400
You didn't?

156
00:10:55,533 --> 00:10:56,200
Let go of her!

157
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:57,433
Hazel!

158
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:03,167
Say it.

159
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:07,267
Say it in front
of my daughter's coffin

160
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,367
that you had nothing
to do with her death.

161
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:11,067
Say it!

162
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:19,233
Because of you,
my child is gone!

163
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:20,933
- That's enough!
- My child is gone!

164
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:24,033
Stop blaming my daughter!

165
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:26,567
Coleen didn't push Jessica.

166
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:30,133
Stop defending
your lying child.

167
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,933
My daughter isn't a liar.

168
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:35,867
Prove in court

169
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:39,167
that she had nothing to do
with Jessica's death.

170
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:40,767
Hazel, that's enough!

171
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:44,500
Don't you have any sense
of time or place?

172
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:48,767
This is Jessica's wake.
Show some respect.

173
00:11:49,933 --> 00:11:51,500
And I'm the one
being disrespectful?

174
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:54,700
Look at you bringing
these people here

175
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:56,400
who weren't even invited!

176
00:11:57,267 --> 00:12:03,033
You don't need an invitation
to pay respects.

177
00:12:03,967 --> 00:12:10,833
We came because this was
our children's sibling who died.

178
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:12,867
I don't care.

179
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:15,333
My child doesn't need
any respect

180
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,667
from the woman who killed her!

181
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:19,500
Please calm down.

182
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:21,700
- Mom, that's enough!
- Stop!

183
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,367
Come on, let's go.

184
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,167
Mom, let's go. Let her be.

185
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:29,600
Go on, Manuel.
I'll wait for you outside.

186
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:38,367
Manuel, did you really
have to bring them here?

187
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,133
You're being insulting.

188
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:44,433
You clearly have no regard
for how I feel.

189
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,300
Hazel, this isn't about you.

190
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,700
They went because Jessica
is the one who died.

191
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:55,300
I'm Jessica's mother,
and what you did is an insult!

192
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,733
Fine, say you were disrespected.

193
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:01,600
But what are you doing,
making a scene?

194
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:04,767
Aren't you disrespecting
Jessica by acting like this?

195
00:13:19,733 --> 00:13:21,600
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

196
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:24,733
I'm sorry.

197
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:29,733
Manuel...

198
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:33,233
Our daughter's gone.

199
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:37,367
She's gone.

200
00:13:40,733 --> 00:13:42,033
What am I supposed to do now?

201
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:02,967
See? I told you we shouldn't
have come here.

202
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,300
Did you see what Hazel did?
She hurt Coleen!

203
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:08,933
If this wasn't Jessica's wake,

204
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:11,667
I'd have shoved that woman
into the coffin myself.

205
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:14,733
Hazel should be buried alive!

206
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,300
I'm sorry, Mom.

207
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,667
It's just that whenever
we talk about Hazel,

208
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,833
I can't stop myself from
saying things I shouldn't.

209
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,433
Dear, that's enough.

210
00:14:29,567 --> 00:14:31,667
Don't let what Hazel
said get to you.

211
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:37,567
Mom, I just wanted to see
Jessica again.

212
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:42,100
I just wanted to say sorry
one more time,

213
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:45,333
even if it's just in front
of her coffin.

214
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,033
That's okay, sweetie.

215
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:50,500
Especially when there
are things left unresolved.

216
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:53,367
But that doesn't make
it your fault, okay?

217
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,167
Our older brother is right.

218
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:00,867
That's the only thing
you need to remember.

219
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:03,500
You're not to blame.

220
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:08,833
That's what I keep
telling myself.

221
00:15:08,967 --> 00:15:12,200
But I can't help
but feel guilty.

222
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:18,533
It's normal to feel
that way, sweetheart.

223
00:15:18,667 --> 00:15:21,500
But don't punish yourself.

224
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:24,700
You tried to save your sister.

225
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:28,700
But what if Hazel
insists otherwise?

226
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:33,833
If someone had seen us before I
accidentally let go of Jessica,

227
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:38,767
they might think
I really pushed her.

228
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:41,133
What do you mean?

229
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:52,800
Jessica, dear.

230
00:15:55,867 --> 00:15:59,000
Do you remember what
you told me once?

231
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:04,167
<i>Dad, just hold me.
Don't let me go.</i>

232
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:07,233
<i>My sweet little girl
just wanted to be held.</i>

233
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:10,200
<i> Dad, please don't leave me.</i>

234
00:16:10,367 --> 00:16:12,467
<i> Don't leave.</i>

235
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:15,567
Why did you leave me?

236
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:20,267
Dear, why did you leave me?

237
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:28,400
Don't you know you're
the reason I kept going?

238
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,933
You were my strength, dear.

239
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:39,567
You were everything to me...

240
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:43,667
when we were in Saudi Arabia...

241
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:46,000
and in Canada.

242
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,400
You were everything, Jessica.

243
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:56,200
Why did you leave me, dear?

244
00:16:57,667 --> 00:17:01,100
Why?

245
00:17:03,767 --> 00:17:06,233
Why, Jessica?

246
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,267
- Jessica, my dear.
- That's enough, Manuel.

247
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,933
Please, that's enough.

248
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:16,700
I swear to you.

249
00:17:17,733 --> 00:17:20,067
I will find the person
who ran into you.

250
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:23,900
I will make that
damned killer pay.

251
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:27,467
Manuel, it's Coleen.

252
00:17:28,633 --> 00:17:30,767
She killed Jessica.

253
00:17:31,767 --> 00:17:35,667
She pushed her, and that's why
our child was hit.

254
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,400
Hazel, please.

255
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:41,100
Stop accusing Coleen.

256
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,667
She's not capable
of killing anyone.

257
00:17:46,167 --> 00:17:49,467
We were arguing outside, Mom.

258
00:17:49,633 --> 00:17:55,500
I pulled her because
I wanted to apologize.

259
00:17:55,633 --> 00:17:59,167
I wanted to talk
about our issues.

260
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:02,000
But she wouldn't listen, Mom.

261
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:04,600
<i>- Jessica!
- Coleen, stop!</i>

262
00:18:04,733 --> 00:18:08,033
We were pulling at each other...

263
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:09,000
and then...

264
00:18:09,133 --> 00:18:09,967
<i>- Jessica, please!
- No!</i>

265
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,733
<i>- Let me go!
- Jessica!</i>

266
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:12,833
<i> Jessica!</i>

267
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:16,733
I accidentally let go of her,
Mom.

268
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:22,200
Someone could think
I pushed her.

269
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:24,367
That's the problem.

270
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:27,600
If Hazel finds a witness,

271
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,500
she might force them to say
that Coleen pushed Jessica.

272
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,167
Don't think that way.

273
00:18:35,467 --> 00:18:42,333
Whoever saw it will say
what really happened.

274
00:18:42,467 --> 00:18:44,067
Mom's right.

275
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,400
Is that what she said?

276
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:51,133
And you believed her?

277
00:18:52,667 --> 00:18:54,000
Manuel...

278
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:58,000
Coleen killed Jessica.

279
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:02,400
Stop defending
your criminal daughter.

280
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:05,867
Don't you dare call
Coleen a criminal.

281
00:19:06,433 --> 00:19:08,533
Felma raised her right.

282
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:21,967
Hello, Joel?

283
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:25,700
<i> Okay. Okay, got it.</i>

284
00:19:26,233 --> 00:19:26,867
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

285
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:34,033
Joel got a copy of the CCTV from
the Traffic Authority, Mom.

286
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:36,267
He's on his way
to the house now.

287
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,933
All right. You all go ahead.

288
00:19:39,067 --> 00:19:40,200
I'll wait here for your dad,

289
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:42,600
then take him back
to the hospital.

290
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:45,100
Call Attorney Yeban, okay?

291
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:46,367
Yes, Mom. I got this.

292
00:19:48,267 --> 00:19:49,467
Okay.

293
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:57,500
I can't believe this.

294
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:01,767
Our daughter is gone,

295
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:05,267
and you're still defending
your illegitimate child?

296
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:08,500
I'm not defending anyone.

297
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:14,767
You're not defending anyone?

298
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:17,833
But everything you say
shows otherwise.

299
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:19,133
Why?

300
00:20:19,267 --> 00:20:23,400
How long have you spent with
Coleen to know she's innocent?

301
00:20:23,533 --> 00:20:26,333
Enough time to see that
she's a good person.

302
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:28,333
She's a good daughter.

303
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:31,167
Coleen isn't capable
of killing anyone.

304
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:34,000
What about you?
Are you sure she's guilty?

305
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,367
Yes, because she has a motive.

306
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:40,433
She's jealous of Jessica.

307
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:41,800
They're enemies.

308
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,000
Hazel, a childish quarrel
is never enough

309
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,967
to call someone a killer.

310
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:48,500
Coleen couldn't
have killed her!

311
00:20:48,633 --> 00:20:50,567
<i> Childish quarrel?</i>

312
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:55,900
My child is in that coffin, and
you call it a childish quarrel?

313
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:58,700
Your daughter isn't even
a minor anymore!

314
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:03,700
Manuel, Hazel, can we just
have a ceasefire?

315
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:05,333
You're standing in front
of your child right now.

316
00:21:05,467 --> 00:21:07,067
There are so many people.
Aren't you ashamed?

317
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,200
No.

318
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:10,400
Manuel is being rude.

319
00:21:10,533 --> 00:21:12,467
She's not giving
Jessica any respect.

320
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:15,767
He's openly defending
his illegitimate child

321
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:16,900
who killed ours!

322
00:21:17,033 --> 00:21:19,900
Coleen didn't kill Jessica!

323
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,600
I'll prove it, Manuel!

324
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:24,433
I'll find evidence
against her!

325
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:27,067
Hazel, come on. That's enough.

326
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:31,333
You won't find a thing
because Coleen is innocent!

327
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:34,067
You really won't stop
defending your criminal child?

328
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,833
No, Hazel.

329
00:21:35,967 --> 00:21:40,433
Because I know. I'm sure
that Coleen is innocent.

330
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:43,133
And stop saying she has
a criminal mind.

331
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:45,267
She's nothing like you!

332
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:46,367
You beast!

333
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,867
- You should go.
- Mrs. Cruz, that's enough!

334
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,633
Take care of Mrs. Cruz.

335
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:53,000
I got him.

336
00:21:53,133 --> 00:21:54,333
Get lost!

337
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,967
Come on. Please stop!

338
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,833
Monster.

339
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:11,800
Sweetie.

340
00:22:12,367 --> 00:22:14,467
Sweetie, I'm sorry.

341
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:17,267
I'm sorry, sweetie.

342
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,500
I'm sorry.

343
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:23,033
I'm sorry. Sorry, dear.

344
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:34,500
Attorney, I want Coleen
held accountable.

345
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:42,967
Mrs. Cruz,
your accusation is serious.

346
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:48,767
If you can prove that Coleen
actually pushed Jessica,

347
00:22:49,967 --> 00:22:51,900
we could charge her
with reckless imprudence

348
00:22:52,033 --> 00:22:53,800
resulting in homicide.

349
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:58,500
If there's proof
she intended to kill,

350
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,333
then we can go for murder.

351
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:06,500
But, Mrs. Cruz,
I must remind you.

352
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:11,600
Words alone won't do.

353
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:14,833
We need solid evidence.

354
00:23:14,967 --> 00:23:17,600
And witnesses.

355
00:23:17,733 --> 00:23:20,100
That's how we can prove it
in court.

356
00:23:20,233 --> 00:23:22,733
What if I find one?

357
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:24,467
Then we can proceed.

358
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:29,500
File a criminal complaint
with the prosecutor.

359
00:23:29,633 --> 00:23:35,700
But, Mrs. Cruz, don't focus
all your anger on Coleen.

360
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:40,000
They're insisting
she didn't push Jessica.

361
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:42,733
Honestly, if I were you,

362
00:23:42,867 --> 00:23:46,867
I'd start by tracking down
that fleeing driver.

363
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:50,667
What I mean is...

364
00:23:52,167 --> 00:23:56,333
don't let your anger
take control.

365
00:23:57,367 --> 00:24:01,967
Because if we let
the hatred steer the case,

366
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:04,933
we might lose sight
of the real culprit.

367
00:24:05,067 --> 00:24:08,867
It'll be harder to bring
justice for Jessica.

368
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,467
The driver was the one
who ran over my child.

369
00:24:14,167 --> 00:24:17,633
But Coleen was the one
who killed Jessica.

370
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:23,300
I'll make sure that
woman rots in prison.

371
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:35,367
Is there any news from the
police investigation, Attorney?

372
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:38,867
They say they've found
an abandoned pick-up truck.

373
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,800
The police can't confirm yet,

374
00:24:40,933 --> 00:24:42,767
but there's a dent
in the bumper,

375
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:48,333
right where the footage
shows Jessica got hit.

376
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:51,300
Manuel, you should go
to the funeral

377
00:24:51,433 --> 00:24:52,900
because you're her father.

378
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:54,967
Hazel will just make a scene.

379
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:59,433
I just want her to have peace,
even in her last moments.

380
00:24:59,567 --> 00:25:00,933
What are you doing here?

381
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:03,800
I'm just asking you
to let Manuel go.

382
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:06,833
Let him attend
Jessica's funeral.

383
00:25:06,967 --> 00:25:11,633
I'll allow him, but only
if you turn Coleen in.

384
00:25:11,767 --> 00:25:13,267
Make her admit to the crime.

385
00:25:14,033 --> 00:25:18,033
I'm sorry, Manuel,
but I won't turn Coleen in.

386
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:20,467
She's innocent.

387
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:25,433
If I have to surrender
myself for dad, I'll do it.
